The paper discusses a computational framework for replicating aspects of human concept learning, which involves visual perception, working memory, and action control. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper focuses on visual perception and manipulation, which could place it under computer vision (cs.CV) and systems and control (cs.SY).
